&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;Paystand is hiring an analyst to build the operational intelligence layer behind our payments business. You&#39;ll own dashboards, models, reporting workflows, and AI-enabled tooling that give leadership clear visibility into payment performance, margin trends, vendor costs, and operational risk. This role sits at the intersection of payments analytics, business operations, and automation, and connects directly to revenue operations and strategic decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;This is not an AI engineering role. It&#39;s for someone who thinks in systems, learns fast, and uses modern tools to produce sharper, faster, more repeatable analysis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;Build and maintain dashboards and KPI frameworks covering margin, success rates, vendor costs, routing performance, pricing, and exceptions. Develop forecasting models and scenario analyses around vendor changes, processor decisions, pricing, and operational improvements. Identify recurring reporting and reconciliation tasks that can be automated or templated. Use AI-assisted tools to accelerate analysis, surface anomalies, and generate reliable business insights. Partner with Data Engineering, Finance, Product, and Payments teams to improve data quality and metric definitions. Document methodologies and model logic so insights become repeatable operating infrastructure.&lt;/p&gt;
